{
  "text": "For this purpose, also the scale evolution of the coupling is parameterized by an interpolating polynomial of the form \u03c3(u) = u + \u03c3 0 u 2 + \u03c3 1 u 3 + . . . , for which the exact results of the corresponding fit (and its covariance matrix) were available from [CITATION_1] 42] . Since the errors on the step scaling functions stem from different simulation runs and are hence uncorrelated, the errors on the fit parameters in the polynomials for \u03c3(u), \u03c3 stat A (u) and those on the recursion coefficients u k , v k calculated from them can be estimated and passed through the recursion straightforwardly by the standard error propagation rules. ",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "15558526"
  },
  "bib_entries": {
    "15558526": {
      "title": "Non-perturbative quark mass renormalization in two-flavor QCD",
      "abstract": "Abstract The running of renormalized quark masses is computed in lattice QCD with two flavors of massless O ( a ) improved Wilson quarks. The regularization and flavor independent factor that relates running quark masses to the renormalization group invariant ones is evaluated in the Schrodinger functional scheme. Using existing data for the scale r 0 and the pseudoscalar meson masses, we define a reference quark mass in QCD with two degenerate quark flavors. We then compute the renormalization group invariant reference quark mass at three different lattice spacings. Our estimate for the continuum value is converted to the strange quark mass with the help of chiral perturbation theory."
    }
  }
}